  "text": "Policymakers would benefit from the collection and dissemination of more official data on off-duty police misconduct and crime. The call for more data on off-duty misbehavior follows initiatives to expand the Law Enforcement Management and Administrative Statistics (LEMAS) survey to include data on use of force complaints (United States Department of Justice, 2003) , as well as [CITATION_1] argument for the collection and release of comprehensive data on all coercive activities including disciplinary actions. The collection of official data on the criminal arrests of police officers-including those that commit crimes while they are technically off-duty-should be incorporated in these initiatives.",
